PROJECT CONTEXT  – CSDC ATTENDANCE SYSTEM
full-stack web application for a college tech club called **Chathurya Student Developer Club (CSDC)**.

The system is a **QR-based event attendance platform**.

The **React frontend is already built**, and the backend is being integrated using **Node.js, Express, and MongoDB (Atlas)**.

Frontend stack:
React
React Router
Tailwind CSS
DaisyUI

Frontend folder structure:

src/
components/
Navbar.jsx
Sidebar.jsx

pages/
Login.jsx
Register.jsx
Dashboard.jsx
Profile.jsx
Events.jsx
QR.jsx
About.jsx

data/
users.js
activities.js

App.jsx
main.jsx

public/
logo.png

Frontend behavior:

Login page
Uses **username + password** (NOT email).

Register page
Registers a user.

Dashboard page shows:
• Member search
• Stats cards (members, events, attendance count)
• Recent activities

Profile page route:

/profile/:username

Displays:
• Avatar
• Name
• Member ID
• Email
• QR Code
• Event timeline

Profile page shows the user's QR code (memberId).

Events page workflow:

Create Event → Activate Event → QR Scanner marks attendance.

About page shows club info and logo.

Navbar appears across pages.
Sidebar opens from the navbar.

Sidebar items:
• Profile
• Events (Attendance)
• About

